's complete first and middle names."},{"number":2,"category":"character","header":"Both parents died when he was a teenager","body":"His father John Marquand died in 1960 when Lonny was seventeen. Adelaide followed three years later, and he spent his life looking for somewhere to call home."},{"number":3,"category":"death","header":"Returned to Cape Cod in his final years","body":"Bipolar diagnosis shaped his middle decades after his parents' early deaths. He died at the Dennis house in 2021, age seventy-seven."}],"cross_connections":[],"career":[{"role":"Patron + underwriter","location":"Asheville NC","notes":"Underwrote the Black Mountain Music Festival the year it was beamed via Mountain Stage into the Former Soviet Union from Asheville NC. Devotee of authentic American 'classical' folk music.","organization":"Black Mountain Music Festival"}],"naming_inspiration":[{"name_element":"Elon Huntington Hooker","inspired_by_id":"H03434","description":"Bears the complete given name of his maternal grandfather Elon Huntington Hooker, founder of the Hooker Electrochemical Company. The only great-grandchild in this Hooker line to inherit the patriarch's full first + middle names as a personal name."}],"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"elon-marquand-1943"}},"burialCemetery":null,"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}